    "However, well-trained deep learning models can focus on details that may be imperceptible to the human eye, potentially addressing this limitation.",
    "Hemdan et al.",
    "34 introduced COVIDX-Net, an AI model capable of automatically detecting COVID-19 positivity in patients based on chest X-ray images.",
    "It achieved a classification accuracy of 91% when tested on a dataset of 75 individuals, with 25 confirmed positive cases and 50 negative cases.",
    "Sethy and Behera 35 utilized a pre-trained transfer technique called ResNet-50 to extract imaging features from COVID-19 patients and employed support vector machines (SVM) for classification, achieving a classification accuracy score of 95.348%."
